1. Install OpenJDK 11 (including javac):

sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-11-jdk

2. Verify Java and Javac Installation:

java -version
javac -version

3. Create and Edit a Java Program:

nano HelloWorld.java

Add the code:

public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
    }
}

Save and exit (Press CTRL + X, then Y, and Enter).
4. Compile the Java Program:

javac HelloWorld.java

5. Run the Java Program:

java HelloWorld

This will output:

Hello, World!

That's the basic setup and flow to write, compile, and run a Java program on Ubuntu.
